%N A014609 a(n) = (5n)!/(5!^n).
%C A014609 a(n) is also the constant term in product 1 <= i,j <= n, i different from j (1 - x_i/x_j)^5. - Sharon Sela (sharonsela(AT)hotmail.com), Feb 18 2002
%D A014609 George E. Andrews, Richard Askey, and Ranjan Roy, Special Functions, Cambridge University Press, 1998.
%H A014609 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A014609/b014609.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..105</a>
%H A014609 Jean-Christophe Novelli and Jean-Yves Thibon, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aam.2020.102019">Hopf algebras of m-permutations, (m + 1)-ary trees, and m-parking functions</a>, Advances in Applied Mathematics, Vol. 117 (2020), 102019; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1403.5962">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:1403.5962 [math.CO], 2014-2020.
%F A014609 a(n) ~ sqrt(Pi) * 5^(4*n+1/2) * n^(5*n+1/2) / (2^(3*n-1/2) * 3^n * exp(5*n)). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 09 2026
%t A014609 a[n_] := (5*n)!/(120^n); Array[a, 11, 0] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 09 2026 *)
%o A014609 (PARI) a(n)=if(n<0,0,(5*n)!/120^n)
